description: John McCarthy This week, we returned from a wonderful family vacation in Maui.    While on vacation, during the travel, and after I arrived home, I've done a lot of thinking.  A whole lot.  Just a bunch of random stuff running through the brain, and I thought that I would take a few minutes to jot them down in a post.  So, in no particular order, here are several things that have been running through my brain:  *  Maui is stunningly beautiful!  Love it there!  *  I am very, very fortunate.....by many measures.  I have a beautiful wife and son, and we're healthy.  Our whole family has clothes, shelter and plenty of food.  We have families that care about us.  I have wonderful, loving parents,  Joan McCarthy  and brothers,  Jeff McCarthy  and  Jim McCarthy .  I have cousins that are living examples of love and laughter.   Jim Wenzell ,  Mike Wenzell ,  Colleen Wenzell Pflanz ,  Maureen Wenzell Smith ,  James Gus Wenzell ,  Tim Wenzell ,  Kassie Fitzgerald Wenzell    Bryan Pflanz  are these living examples.....   *  I love walks on the beach.  I got up early to walk on the beach most of the days on our vacation, and it was such an exhilarating experience.  Peaceful.  Beautiful.  I just love it!  *  I thought about my brother, Jeff McCarthy, and how he has spent so much time traveling the world.  (Over the last two months, he's been in Spain, Malta and Italy).  I'm just so happy for him.  So many people talk about what they "would" do, but Jeff "does" it.  He's LIVING, EXPERIENCING AND DOING.  Congratulations,  Jeff McCarthy !  *  I've been thinking about my old high school friend,  Mark Postak .  I've been thinking about his tremendous pride in being a Grizzly, and about how he's done such an incredible job of keeping in touch with so many fellow Grizzlies, who are now spread out throughout the country.  He's a "glue" guy, and a "connector".  He has a wife, a child with disabilities and another young child, yet he spends so much time "lifting others up" and being such a positive force in the lives of so many.  Thank you, Mark!  You are a special one.  *  I thought about the recent opportunity that I've been given with TeamSmile.  I truly thank Dr.  Bill Busch  for the faith in me.  I'm really energized about TeamSmile.  *  I thought a lot about Small College Basketball.  I find it to be thrilling and exhilarating to do things that haven't been done before.  It's such a thrill to serve the great game of basketball; in particular, to serve the coaches, players, contributors and all those involved with the game of basketball at the small college levels.  I'm pleased with what we've accomplished thus far, and I'm very (VERY) excited about the future of Small College Basketball.  Much to come.  *  Whether I'm thinking about family, TeamSmile or Small College Basketball......or other things that are worthwhile in life, I've thought about the importance of relationships.  TeamSmile is the brainchild of Founder  Bill Busch , but it takes many dedicated people to fulfill the vision of Dr. Busch.  Small College Basketball is my personal brainchild, but it clearly takes many, many other people to believe in the vision (and in me, personally), to bring the ideas to life.    *  I've been thinking about those that spend (or have spent) a great deal of time FOR others or FOR a cause.  Those people are special, and they are leading a life of meaning and fulfillment.  *  I've been thinking about people that express themselves really well on Facebook.  In particular, I often like to read the posts from  Roy Alan Firestone ,  Robert Valvano ,  Jeff Pearlman  and  Ralph Turner .  They put a lot of thought and passion into their posts.  *  Deep, personal relationships are key to the creation of real fulfillment in life.  *  I relate very well - and truly appreciate - people that live with passion.  It doesn't matter where the passion lies (unless it's destructive or negative), I love to watch people LIVE their passion.    *  There is incredible beauty in nature.    *  My son, Sean, really likes snorkeling, beach volleyball, pickle ball and soccer.    *  I really enjoy good books, but the more I learn, the more that I realize that I have soooo much more to learn......  *  I love good movies.  (I watched Zero Dark 40 on one of the flights, and it was riveting).  *  I really do have a wonderful wife,  Christine Beach McCarthy . John McCarthy
